This project presents a comprehensive Walmart Dashboard developed in Power BI, designed to deliver actionable insights and support data-driven decision-making. The dashboard serves as a powerful tool for monitoring and analyzing sales performance across various dimensions.


Key Features

Key Performance Indicators (KPIs): 
Displays crucial metrics, including total sales, profit margins, average order value, and year-over-year growth, giving a high-level overview of business performance.
Dynamic Visualizations:
Leverages interactive charts, bar graphs, line graphs, and geographic maps to present data in an intuitive and visually engaging manner.
Trend Analysis: 
Tracks sales trends over time to identify seasonal fluctuations and forecast future performance.
Drill-Down Capabilities: 
Allows users to filter and analyze data at granular levels, such as by region, product category, or specific timeframes.
Usability: 
Designed with user-friendly navigation and interactive slicers to enhance the analytical experience.


Business Impact

This dashboard empowers business stakeholders to:

Identify Trends: 
Understand historical sales performance and spot emerging trends.
Optimize Strategy: 
Pinpoint underperforming regions or categories and take corrective actions.
Enhance Decision-Making: 
Use data to inform strategic business decisions with clarity and confidence.


Technical Details
Tools Used: 
Power BI for visualization, DAX for data modeling, and data cleaning techniques.
Data Sources:
Aggregated sales data from Walmart, segmented by time, region, and category.


This project highlights expertise in business intelligence, data visualization, and advanced analytics while addressing real-world challenges in sales and performance management.
